				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Bregalad wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">it's not possible to have more than one mapper at a time.</div><br />The MMC3 multicarts already have two mappers at once: one for the game to use and one to select a game. In the case of mappers with Famicom expansion sound, you're correct that only one mapper can control the PRG ROM address lines, but multiple mappers can listen for writes. In fact, several Jaleco games have sampled sound as a separate chip from the mapper. Along the same lines, I remember reading about a project where <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?p=25067#p25067" class="postlink">someone rigged up an MP3 player that plays through the Famicom audio path</a>, at which point chip games can use essentially CD music.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

